    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-and-cream-tortiglioni-with-asparagus-and-pine-nut-with-side/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> pasta</strong>, reserving 125ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[165ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [225ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-and-cream-tortiglioni-with-asparagus-and-pine-nut-with-side/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pine nuts</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once toasted, transfer the<strong> pine nuts</strong> to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-and-cream-tortiglioni-with-asparagus-and-pine-nut-with-side/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, trim the woody ends off your <strong>asparagus </strong>and discard</p><p>Chop the <strong>asparagus tips </strong>away from the stalks, then roughly chop the <strong>asparagus stalks</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-and-cream-tortiglioni-with-asparagus-and-pine-nut-with-side/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-and-cream-tortiglioni-with-asparagus-and-pine-nut-with-side/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong> with the <strong>chopped asparagus</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>soft cheese</strong> with your <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the asparagus is tender and the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic, chilli & cream sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-and-cream-tortiglioni-with-asparagus-and-pine-nut-with-side/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cooked pasta </strong>to the pan with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>garlic, chilli & cream pasta with asparagus</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/garlic-chilli-and-cream-tortiglioni-with-asparagus-and-pine-nut-with-side/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>garlic, chilli & cream pasta with asparagus</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and the <strong>toasted pine nuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
